The paper discusses the vulnerability of convolutional neural networks to adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also explores the use of regularization techniques and ensembles, which are common approaches in the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.CR, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
